OL,3,CVilla's Roman mosaic floor
OL,4,Cpainstakingly recreated over five years
OL,6,FThe mosaic floor of a Roman villa has
OL,7,Fbeen painstakingly recreated in
OL,8,FSomerset using 140,000 cubes of stone
OL,9,Fand tile.
OL,11,FIt's thought the floor in the Roman
OL,12,Fdining room reconstruction at Avalon
OL,13,FArchaeology is the only one in the UK
OL,14,Fmade entirely by untrained volunteers.
OL,16,FRoughly 25 of them have been involved
OL,17,Fin making the mosaic over the last
OL,18,Ffive years, working one day a week,
OL,19,Fwith between two and five people
OL,20,Finvolved each day.
