OL,3,CVilla's Roman mosaic floor
OL,4,Cpainstakingly recreated over five years
OL,6,FThe stone used for the mosaic cubes is
OL,7,Fthe same local material that the
OL,8,FRomans used, with white, blue and grey
OL,9,Flias, yellow Doulting stone, and red
OL,10,Fmade from tiles.
OL,12,FThe individual cubes were created
OL,13,Fusing a hammer and a 'hardie' - which
OL,14,Fis similar to a chisel set upright in
OL,15,Fa block of wood - and were laid in a
OL,16,Fbed of lime mortar.
OL,18,FThe inspiration for the design
