OL,3,CVilla's Roman mosaic floor
OL,4,Cpainstakingly recreated over five years
OL,6,FAccording to experts at Avalon
OL,7,FArchaeology, Roman mosaic elephants in
OL,8,Fcontinental Europe usually appear more
OL,9,Frealistic and have the correct size of
OL,10,Fears.
OL,12,FHowever, historically British
OL,13,Fmosaicists seem to have been more
OL,14,Fconservative in their ear depictions -
OL,15,Fperhaps because they had never seen an
OL,16,Felephant and so couldn't imagine an
OL,17,Fanimal having such big ears in
OL,18,Frelation to its head.
