OL,3,CVilla's Roman mosaic floor
OL,4,Cpainstakingly recreated over five years
OL,6,FThe Romans often included optical
OL,7,Fillusions in their frescoes and
OL,8,Fmosaics. One example is a design from
OL,9,Fthe Newton St Loe villa.
OL,11,FSome people see a flower, or star, or
OL,12,Ffour converging cubes, or four
OL,13,Fconverging Toblerone shapes.
OL,15,FThe dolphin
OL,17,FThe dolphin design was inspired by
OL,18,FLopen villa in the south of Somerset,
OL,19,Fwhich was discovered by chance in 2001.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
